The infringing page contains text from my original article.

The only text on the infringing page that is not taken from the original article is "Dell has recently reveal its latest special edition Inspiron I15RSE-6167BK. The Dell Inspiron I15RSE-6167BK features" and "The Dell Inspiron I15RSE-6167BK price $950".

Everything else is taken from the original article.

"...sports anodized aluminum palm rests and lid with precision-etched honeycomb design." is taken from the 2nd paragraph of the original article. 

"The entertainment-oriented Dell Inspiron I15RSE-6167BK packs 8GB of DDR3 memory, which is more than sufficient for virtually any computing task and multitasking" is taken from the 5th paragraph of the original.

The whole paragraph after "Dell Inspiron I15RSE-6167BK Specifications" subtitle on the infringing page is copied from the original article (the last paragraph, under "Dell Inspiron I15RSE-6167BK Specifications" subtitle).

Images are not a part of this DMCA complaint.
